Given the two equations:
\[2010a + 2014b = 2018 \quad \text{(Equation 1)}\]
\[2012a + 2016b = 2020 \quad \text{(Equation 2)}\]

Step 1: Subtract Equation 2 from Equation 1 to eliminate $a$ and find an equation in terms of $b$ only.
\begin{align*}
(2012a + 2016b) - (2010a + 2014b) &= 2020 - 2018 \\
(2012a - 2010a) + (2016b - 2014b) &= 2 \\
2a + 2b &= 2
\end{align*}

Step 2: Simplify the equation from Step 1 to isolate $a + b$.
\begin{align*}
2a + 2b &= 2 \\
a + b &= 1 \quad \text{(Equation 3)}
\end{align*}

Step 3: Multiply Equation 3 by 2010 to align the coefficient of $a$ with that in Equation 1, facilitating the elimination of $a$.
\begin{align*}
2010(a + b) &= 2010 \\
2010a + 2010b &= 2010
\end{align*}

Step 4: Subtract the result from Step 3 from Equation 1 to find the value of $b$.
\begin{align*}
(2010a + 2014b) - (2010a + 2010b) &= 2018 - 2010 \\
2014b - 2010b &= 8 \\
4b &= 8
\end{align*}

Step 5: Solve for $b$.
\begin{align*}
4b &= 8 \\
b &= 2
\end{align*}

Step 6: Substitute the value of $b$ back into Equation 3 to find the value of $a$.
\begin{align*}
a + b &= 1 \\
a + 2 &= 1
\end{align*}

Step 7: Solve for $a$.
\[ a = 1 - 2 = -1 \]

Step 8: Calculate $a - b$ using the values obtained for $a$ and $b$.
\[ a - b = (-1) - 2 = -3 \]

Final Answer: -3.0

