Step 6: We expand the squared term to get a quadratic equation:
\begin{align*}
(y^2 + 18y + 81) + y^2 &= 153
\end{align*}

Step 7: Combining like terms, we simplify the equation to:
\begin{align*}
2y^2 + 18y + 81 &= 153
\end{align*}

Step 8: To make it easier to factor, we move all terms to one side to get:
\begin{align*}
2y^2 + 18y - 72 &= 0
\end{align*}

Step 9: Divide every term in the equation by $2$ to simplify the quadratic equation further:
