answer:
To find the value of $f(7)$ for the given function $f(x)=\dfrac{5x+1}{x-1}$, we will substitute $x$ with the number $7$.

Step 1: Substitute $7$ for $x$ in the function.
\begin{align*}
f(7) &= \dfrac{5(7)+1}{7-1}
\end{align*}

Step 2: Multiply $5$ by $7$ and add $1$ to find the numerator.
\begin{align*}
f(7) &= \dfrac{5 \times 7 + 1}{7-1} \\
&= \dfrac{35 + 1}{7 - 1}
\end{align*}

Step 3: Perform the addition in the numerator and the subtraction in the denominator.
\begin{align*}
f(7) &= \dfrac{35 + 1}{7 - 1} \\
&= \dfrac{36}{6}
\end{align*}

Step 4: Divide the numerator by the denominator to simplify the fraction and find the value of $f(7)$.
\begin{align*}
f(7) &= \dfrac{36}{6} \\
&= 6
\end{align*}

Final Answer: 6.0

