t-3 &= 0 \quad \text{or} \quad t-9 = 0
\end{align*}

Step 5: Solve for $t$ in each case:
\begin{align*}
t &= 3 \quad \text{or} \quad t = 9
\end{align*}

Step 6: Analyze the context of the problem. We are seeking the largest value of $t$, so we choose the greater of the two solutions.

